Update process:
1. Base image digest:
   - Inspect the current multi-arch manifest index for ubuntu:24.04.
   - Example: docker buildx imagetools inspect ubuntu:24.04
   - Example: docker buildx imagetools inspect ubuntu:24.04 --format '{{json .Manifest}}' | jq -r .digest
   - Verify the digest resolves for both amd64 and arm64.
   - Example: docker buildx imagetools inspect ubuntu:24.04 --format '{{json .Manifest}}' | jq '.manifests[].platform'
2. Docker Compose:
   - Check https://github.com/docker/compose/releases for the next version tag.
   - Update COMPOSE_VERSION below and keep the versioned GitHub release URL.
3. npm packages:
   - Check each package with npm view <package> version
   - Update the pinned version in the relevant npm install command:
     - npm view @google/gemini-cli version
     - npm view @openai/codex version
     - npm view @playwright/mcp version
4. Verification:
   - Run go test ./... after every version bump.
   - Build a sandbox image on both amd64 and arm64 if the base digest changes.

Validation tools update procedure:
1. kubectl:
   - Releases: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/releases and https://dl.k8s.io/release/stable.txt
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/kubernetes/kubernetes/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for dl.k8s.io binary paths
2. helm:
   - Releases: https://github.com/helm/helm/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/helm/helm/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for linux-amd64/linux-arm64 tarballs
3. kustomize:
   - Releases: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/kustomize/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/kubernetes-sigs/kustomize/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: keep the versioned kustomize%2Fv<version> URL segment and use $(dpkg --print-architecture)
4. yq:
   - Releases: https://github.com/mikefarah/yq/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/mikefarah/yq/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for yq_linux_amd64 / yq_linux_arm64
5. jq:
   - Releases: https://github.com/jqlang/jq/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/jqlang/jq/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Package source: jq is apt-managed here; verify the Ubuntu package version before deciding whether a repo/package-source change is needed
6. opentofu:
   - Releases: https://github.com/opentofu/opentofu/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/opentofu/opentofu/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for tofu_<version>_linux_amd64 / arm64 tarballs
7. tflint:
   - Releases: https://github.com/terraform-linters/tflint/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/terraform-linters/tflint/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for the versioned zip asset names
8. kubeconform:
   - Releases: https://github.com/yannh/kubeconform/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/yannh/kubeconform/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for kubeconform-linux-amd64 / arm64 tarballs
9. kube-linter:
   - Releases: https://github.com/stackrox/kube-linter/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/stackrox/kube-linter/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: inspect release assets because amd64 uses kube-linter-linux.tar.gz while arm64 uses kube-linter-linux_arm64.tar.gz
10. trivy:
   - Releases: https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/aquasecurity/trivy/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: map $(dpkg --print-architecture) to Trivy's 64bit / ARM64 archive names
11. flux:
   - Releases: https://github.com/fluxcd/flux2/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/fluxcd/flux2/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for flux_<version>_linux_amd64 / arm64 tarballs
12. sops:
   - Releases: https://github.com/getsops/sops/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/getsops/sops/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use $(dpkg --print-architecture) for sops-v<version>.linux.amd64 / arm64
13. Validation verification:
   - Update this comment block and the versioned URLs in the validation_tools RUN block in the same commit.
   - Inspect release assets before bumping any multi-arch binary; use gh release view <tag> --repo <org>/<repo> when the filename pattern is unclear.
   - Run go test ./... && go test -v ./integration -count=1 -timeout 20m after every bump.

Exploration tools update procedure:
1. ripgrep:
   - Releases: https://github.com/BurntSushi/ripgrep/releases
   - Check newer package version: docker run --rm ubuntu:24.04 bash -lc 'apt-get update >/dev/null && apt-cache policy ripgrep'
   - Asset naming: apt-managed; use the exact Debian version from apt-cache (for example `14.1.0-1`)
2. fd-find:
   - Releases: https://github.com/sharkdp/fd/releases
   - Check newer package version: docker run --rm ubuntu:24.04 bash -lc 'apt-get update >/dev/null && apt-cache policy fd-find'
   - Asset naming: apt-managed; package is `fd-find`, binary is `/usr/bin/fdfind`, and the image provides `/usr/local/bin/fd`
3. universal-ctags:
   - Releases: https://github.com/universal-ctags/ctags/releases
   - Check newer package version: docker run --rm ubuntu:24.04 bash -lc 'apt-get update >/dev/null && apt-cache policy universal-ctags'
   - Asset naming: apt-managed; use the exact Debian version from apt-cache, including the revision suffix
4. ast-grep:
   - Releases: https://github.com/ast-grep/ast-grep/releases
   - Check newer tag: curl -s https://api.github.com/repos/ast-grep/ast-grep/releases/latest | jq -r .tag_name
   - Asset naming: use app-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu.zip / app-aarch64-unknown-linux-gnu.zip; map dpkg arch to uname -m-style token
